description:
MIRROR COMICS is a Canadian Publisher [active from 2010 to 2015]. It was co-founded by writer-artist-designer Dominic Bercier and entrepreneur Allan Isfan in Ottawa, Canada, in January 2010.

MIRROR COMICS projects include promo art for the Sony Pictures film DEFENDOR, and the prequel comic to the film EDDIE The Sleepwalking Cannibal, as well as the song to comics adaptation of Evanescence : BRING ME TO LIFE.

Its titles include GHOST KING [A Book of Changes], CHALLENGER, LIKE NEVER BEFORE & LIKE NEVER AGAIN [A Comic Book in 24 Hours], THE BIRD CALLER, BIG BOX APOCALYPSE, MISSION ARIZONA, SUNSET COAST, HOLD MY HAND [A Father and Son Book] and ZOMKEYS.

Its digital distribution included MyDigitalComics.com and ComiXolgy.com and its graphic novel BIG BOX APOCALYPSE was released on Diamond in 2014.

It was most active at industry events in Central Canada, namely in Toronto, Ottawa and Montreal and in Atlantic Canada.
name: Mirror Comics

description:
Lucha Comics

Lucha Comics is a Canadian comic book publishing imprint of The Shooting Star Press, that publishes a wide range of genres - ranges from Manga to Historical Fiction. Currently, Lucha Comics publishes digitally, but has plans to publish print products before the end of 2014.

Creators who have produced Lucha Books include Jee Chang, Sohn, James A. Bretney, Jeffery Thompson, Sasha Janowicz, and Tony McDougall.

History

Lucha Comics is a comic book publisher founded by Rodolfo Martinez in 2013, first producing the English translation of Boom!, an independent Korean title. The remainder of 2013 saw Lucha Comics secure agreements to distribute more titles from Korea, The UK, and the U.S. Lucha Comics now distributes on ComiXology, Amazon, Google Play, Drivethru Comics, and ComicsFix.

The Shooting Star Press

The Shooting Star Press inc. is the corporate parent of Lucha Comics. The Shooting Star Press specializes in independent comics books, graphic novels, e-books and mobile games. Its first mobile game will be released under the brand Lucha Games in Q2 2014.

Lucha Comics

Lucha Comics is the comic book & graphic novel publishing arm of The Shooting Star Press. With the tagline "Awesome, independent comics from around the world" Lucha Comics has plans to bring on creators from several countries, including Canada, U.S.A., Mexico, Pakistan, Great Britain, Australia, Russia, Korea, The Philippines, Spain, and more.

Lucha's first title was Boom!, an independent Korean graphic novel written and illustrated by Jee Chang.

Titles

To date, Lucha Comics has secured the rights to publish and distribute the following titles:

  • Boom! (Graphic Novel, One-Shot)
  • Stay (Graphic Novel, One-Shot)
  • Diaries of the Invasion (Ongoing)
  • The Kursk (Ongoing)
  • The Fight We Never Saw (Graphic Novel, One-Shot)
  • Reality (Ongoing)
  • Failsafe
name: Lucha Comics
